Yes i agree, some on here cannot wait to label him as an evil man with premeditation. The right treatment and nobody would have been hurt. I can understand his victims families thinking much worse, but people really should research these cases before throwing out such blame. He killed himself in prison in the end.

An unusual choice to pick because this type of offender is the rarest, far more likely but still very rare is a hot prowl burglar escalating to rape and murder, again the chances are it would never happen.

He was a severely mentally ill man, i am not so sure he was evil. Obviously i am not condoning what he did, the crimes were incredibly depraved. However the people that were tasked with monitoring his illness and treatment just didn't bother.
